verbs.description: ingrapple (third-person singular simple present ingrapples, present participle ingrappling, simple past and past participle ingrappled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To seize; to clutch; to grapple.
examples: Looke how two Lyons fierce, both hungry, both pursue
One sweet and selfe-same prey, at one another flie,
And with their armed pawes ingrappled dreadfully,
